//---------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
// Get the actor with the specified name by looking in this class (or any subclass) and
// assert if no such actor is found.
//
// Params:
//   name: name of the actor to search for
//
// Returns: Actor found (asserts if not found)
//
// Examples:
//   ```
//   // Same as Character@'Bob'
//   !bob: Character.named('Bob')
//
//   bob.do_character_stuff
//   ```
//
// Note:
//   Essentially the same as object id - `ActorClass@'some_name'`
//   `find_named()` is the same but returns nil if not found.
//
// See: find_named()
//---------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

(Symbol name) ThisClass_

